prouerbe in Plato ascribeth trouth to children and dronkennes,
yet maie all the praise therof be chiefly appended
to me, as Euripides can well testifie, who wrote
thus: A foole speaketh like a foole (id est) plainely. For
what soeuer he hath in his thought, that sheweth he also
in his countinaunce, and expresseth it in his talke.
