with the pricke of dredefull furiousnesse. But there
is an other kynde of madnesse, farre vnlike the former,
whiche procedeth from me wholy, and most is to be embraced.
As often as a certaine pleasant rauing, or errour
of the mynde, deliuereth the herte of that man,
whom it possesseth, from all wonted carefulnesse, &amp; rendreth
it dyuers waies, muche recreated with new delectacion.

